## 🚀 What it does

Most people apply to jobs blindly — sending the same CV everywhere and hoping for the best. **JobSense** fixes that.

Upload your CV and paste a job description. The app uses **Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)** to read both documents, cross-reference them using two separate FAISS vector stores, and produces a structured career report telling you exactly:

- ✅ Which skills you already have that the JD wants
- ❌ Which skills are missing (your gaps)
- 💬 5 talking points to use in the interview
- ✍️ 3 rewritten CV bullet points tailored to this specific role
- 📊 A match score (0–100%) so you know where you stand before applying

You can then ask follow-up questions in chat — the bot remembers both documents and the report it generated.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
CV (PDF)          ──► PyMuPDF ──► Text Chunks ──► OpenAI Embeddings ──► FAISS Store A ──┐
                                                                                          ├──► Similarity Search
Job Description   ──► Splitter ──► Text Chunks ──► OpenAI Embeddings ──► FAISS Store B ──┘
                                                                                          │
                                                                         Retrieved Chunks ─┤
                                                                                          ▼
                                                              System Prompt + Context ──► GPT-4o
                                                                                          │
                                                                                          ▼
                                                                         Pydantic Parser ──► Structured JSON Report
                                                                                          │
                                                                                          ▼
                                                                              Streamlit UI ──► You
```

**Why two FAISS stores?** Most RAG tutorials query a single document. This project cross-references two separate vector stores simultaneously — the same pattern used in enterprise systems that query a user profile against a policy database. It's harder to build and more impressive to explain.

---

## 🛠️ Tech stack

| Layer | Technology | Why |
|---|---|---|
| LLM | GPT-4o via LangChain | Best reasoning for structured analysis |
| Vector DB | FAISS (local) | Zero cost, zero latency, no signup needed |
| Embeddings | OpenAI text-embedding-3-small | Fast, cheap, accurate |
| Document parsing | PyMuPDF | Handles real-world messy PDFs reliably |
| Output schema | Pydantic v2 | Guarantees structured JSON every time |
| Memory | ConversationBufferMemory | Follow-up chat remembers full context |
| UI | Streamlit | Deployed and shareable in minutes |
| Orchestration | LangChain LCEL | Clean, readable pipeline: prompt \| llm \| parser |

---

## 📁 Project structure

```
jobsense/
├── app.py           # Streamlit UI — file upload, report rendering, follow-up chat
├── ingest.py        # PDF/text → chunks → embeddings → FAISS vector store
├── generate.py      # Retrieval chain + GPT-4o + Pydantic structured output
├── schema.py        # CareerReport Pydantic model
├── .env             # API keys (not committed)
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚡ Run locally

**1. Clone the repo**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/jobsense.git
cd jobsense
```

**2. Install dependencies**
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**3. Add your API key**
```bash
# Create a .env file
echo "OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here" > .env
```

**4. Run the app**
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

Open `http://localhost:8501` in your browser.

