## 📊 Example output

Given a Senior Python Developer JD and a CV with Django/Flask experience:

```json
{
  "match_score": 74,
  "matched_skills": ["Python", "Django", "REST APIs", "PostgreSQL", "Git"],
  "missing_skills": ["Kubernetes", "AWS Lambda", "Redis"],
  "strengths": [
    "3 years of production Django experience directly matches the JD",
    "Open source contributions demonstrate code quality discipline",
    "PostgreSQL expertise covers the database requirement fully"
  ],
  "rewritten_bullets": [
    "Architected and deployed a Django REST API serving 50k+ daily requests with 99.9% uptime",
    "Reduced query response time by 40% through PostgreSQL indexing and query optimisation",
    "Led migration of monolithic Flask app to microservices, cutting deployment time by 60%"
  ],
  "interview_talking_points": [
    "Lead with your Django production experience — it directly matches their core requirement",
    "Frame your REST API work in terms of scale and uptime, not just features built",
    "For the Kubernetes gap: mention you're actively learning it and show your progress",
    "Use your open source contributions as proof of code review and collaboration skills",
    "Ask them about their current infrastructure pain points — shows strategic thinking"
  ]
}
```

---

## ⚠️ Limitations

- **Scanned PDFs not supported** — needs OCR (Tesseract integration planned)
- **Single session memory** — conversation history resets on page refresh; persistent memory via LangGraph is a planned improvement
- **English only** — prompt engineering optimised for English JDs and CVs
- **No authentication** — single-user design; multi-user support would require per-user FAISS stores

---

## 🗺️ Roadmap

- [ ] Add OCR support for scanned CVs (Tesseract / AWS Textract)
- [ ] Persistent cross-session memory with LangGraph
- [ ] Export report as PDF
- [ ] Support multiple JD comparison (which job fits me best?)
- [ ] RAGAS evaluation score for retrieval quality

